CDIP specializes in wave measurement and analysis, with archives of high-resolution spectral wave data that cover multiple decades for many sites. These sustained, long-term time series are critical for studies on climate, weather, ocean energy, and other subjects. CDIP is funded primarily by the US Army Corps of Engineers and the California Department of Parks and Recreation.</dct:description>         <dcat:keyword>climate</dcat:keyword>
